ct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Pembridge was born in 1474, in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Walter Pembridge, was 29 and her mother, Joan Herbert, was 32. She married John Burley before 1500, in Wiltshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1544, in her hometown, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1474–1544":"1474–1544","–Male":"Surnud","1470–1540":"1470–1540","1501–Male":"1501–Surnud","1445–Male":"1445–Surnud","1443–Female":"1443–Surnud","1501":"1501","before 1500":"enne 1500","1544":"1544","1445":"1445","1443":"1443","1474":"1474","1540":"1540","1470":"1470","about 1540":"umbes 1540","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Poulshot, Wiltshire, England":"Poulshot, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1474–1544":"1474–1544","–Male":"Kuollut","1470–1540":"1470–1540","1501–Male":"1501–Kuollut","1445–Male":"1445–Kuollut","1443–Female":"1443–Kuollut","1501":"1501","before 1500":"ennen vuotta 1500","1544":"1544","1445":"1445","1443":"1443","1474":"1474","1540":"1540","1470":"1470","about 1540":"noin 1540","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Poulshot, Wiltshire, England":"Poulshot, Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1474–1544":"1474–1544","–Male":"Décédé","1470–1540":"1470–1540","1501–Male":"1501–Décédé","1445–Male":"1445–Décédé","1443–Female":"1443–Décédée","1501":"1501","before 1500":"avant 1500","1544":"1544","1445":"1445","1443":"1443","